title.narrative: National child protection policy in place and legislative framework to protect children from violence, abuse and neglect strengthened through the adoption of a national child protection code.

description.narrative:
Important steps were taken to enhance the legal and policy frameworks. The draft Child Protection Code was revised and is being improved, involving all national CP stakeholders. The new CP Policy is now ready for governmental approval and the coordination mechanisms for its implementation and monitoring have been set up at central and decentralized level. The costed Action Plan for Civil registration and vital statistics (CRSV) was endorsed by the government and disseminated among internal and external partners to start mobilizing funding for civil registration.
| Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
